FDLP

The University of Maryland Library serves as a regional depository library under the Federal Depository Library Program (FDLP), established by the Government Printing Office (GPO) in 1813. The goal of the FDLP is to ensure that the public has access to information created by its government, and FDLP depository libraries collect, maintain, preserve and assist users in accessing that information. The University of Maryland Libraries serve as a regional depository library for Maryland, Delaware, and Washington, D.C.

Quick Links

  • AAA - Catalog of U.S. Government Publications (GPO)
    Contains descriptive records for historical and current federal publications and provides direct links to those that are available online.
  • U.S. Census
  • AAA - American Factfinder
    Population, Housing, Economic, and Geographic data from the Census Bureau. Also includes maps, statistics, fact sheets and other publications.
  • The White House
  • AAA - FDsys
    Disseminates official information from all three branches of the US Federal Government.(Formerly GPO Access).
  • The American Presidency Project
  • AAA - Federal Register
    Official daily publication for rules, proposed rules, and notices of federal agencies and organizations, as well as executive orders and other presidential documents.
  • THOMAS (LOC)
    Provides full text of the United States Congress legislation; Congressional Record, committee information, and historical documents.
  • Congress.gov
  • AAA - Data. Gov
    â€œThe home of the U.S. Government's open data." provides data, tools and resources to conduct research, develop web and mobile apps and design data visualizations and much more.
  • AAA - Statistical Abstract of the United States
    Data from 1790 to the present. Covers social and economic conditions in the United States, comprised of data from the Census Bureau, other Federal agencies, and private organizations.
  • A Century of Lawmaking (LOC)
